{#- OPERATOR — who fixes it + fit stats -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-help-missing-transactions-operator" style="padding-top:24px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Who fixes it</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">A Certified ProAdvisor finds the gap and gets the books to tie.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Widening a date range is the easy part. The work that actually restores trust in the numbers is everything a genuine gap leaves behind: tracing where transactions actually landed, re-downloading the missing dates from the bank feed without creating duplicates, using the Audit Log to see what was deleted and by whom, restoring legitimate entries, and re-running reconciliation until each month ties to the bank statement again. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope and verifies the period is complete before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
